{"id":43533,"date":"2025-04-15T11:49:00","date_gmt":"2025-04-15T07:49:00","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/?p=43533"},"modified":"2025-04-15T12:35:25","modified_gmt":"2025-04-15T08:35:25","slug":"white-or-necessary-lies","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2025\/04\/15\/white-or-necessary-lies\/","title":{"rendered":"Hadith on Dishonesty: Telling white lies or necessary lies"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>Asma\u2019 bint Yazid reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201c<strong>It is not allowed to lie except in three cases: a man conversing with his wife to please her, to lie in warfare, and to lie in order to reconcile people.<\/strong>\u201d<\/p>\n<p>Source: Sunan al-Tirmidhi\u0304 1939<\/p>\n<p>Grade: <em>Hasan<\/em> (fair) according to Al-Tirmidhi<\/p>\n<p>Imam al-Khattabi commented, \u201cThese are matters in which a person may be compelled to say more or exaggerate the truth to seek safety and avoid harm. In some situations, a concession has been granted to commit a lesser wrongdoing to achieve a better outcome.\u201d<\/p>\n<p>Source: Sharh\u0323 al-Sunnah lil-Baghawi\u0304 13\/119<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\">\u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u200c\u0623\u064e\u0633\u0652\u0645\u064e\u0627\u0621\u064e \u0628\u0650\u0646\u0652\u062a\u0650 \u064a\u064e\u0632\u0650\u064a\u062f\u064e \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e\u062a\u0652 \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0631\u064e\u0633\u064f\u0648\u0644\u064f \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0647\u0650 \u0635\u064e\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0649 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0647\u064f \u0639\u064e\u0644\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0647\u0650 \u0648\u064e\u0633\u064e\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0645\u064e \u0644\u064e\u0627 \u064a\u064e\u062d\u0650\u0644\u064f\u0651 \u0627\u0644\u0652\u0643\u064e\u0630\u0650\u0628\u064f \u0625\u0650\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0627 \u0641\u0650\u064a \u062b\u064e\u0644\u064e\u0627\u062b\u064d \u064a\u064f\u062d\u064e\u